SIMPLE: aneroid
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aneroid
<hw>An"e*roid</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <grk>'a</grk>
priv. + <grk>nhro`s</grk> wet, moist + <ets>-oid</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>an⟦eacute⟧ro⟦ium⟧de</ets>.]</ety> <def>Containing no liquid; --
said of a kind of barometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Aneroid barometer</b></col>, <cd>a barometer the action
of which depends on the varying pressure of the atmosphere upon the
elastic top of a metallic box (shaped like a watch) from which the air
has been exhausted. An index shows the variation of
pressure.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>aneroid</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: aneroid
<hw>an"e*roid</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An aneroid barometer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>anes</ent>⟦br⟧
